## Styling conventions

Tailwind v4 utility classes only — no custom CSS unless Tailwind can't do it.

Outcome badge colours (consistent everywhere):
- `agreed` → `bg-green-100 text-green-800`
- `rejected` → `bg-red-100 text-red-800`
- `callback` → `bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800`
- `no_answer` → `bg-gray-100 text-gray-700`

Card style: `bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 p-4` or `p-6`.
Page background: `bg-gray-50`.

---

## Coding conventions

- FastAPI route handlers: always `async def`
- SQLAlchemy sessions: `Depends(get_db)` dependency injection only
- Pydantic models for all request/response bodies
- New Python packages: `uv add pkg` from inside `backend/` — never pip
- Timestamps from DB: convert with `new Date(ts).toLocaleTimeString()` in frontend
- Call log sort: always `called_at DESC` — most recent at top
- Never hardcode `localhost:8000` — use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` env var
- Leaflet map: always dynamic import with `{ ssr: false }` in Next.js App Router

